1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:02,567
<i>She was in a relationship
before she left Manila?</i>

2
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:04,267
<i> Peter Montevilla.</i>

3
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:07,400
<i> Hey! Who are you?!</i>

4
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:11,900
<i> Tell me why you're here,</i>

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:13,567
<i>or I'll have you arrested
for trespassing!</i>

6
00:00:13,733 --> 00:00:14,867
<i> Your brother!</i>

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,700
<i>I think he has something to do
why my father is missing!</i>

8
00:00:17,800 --> 00:00:18,733
<i> His name is Sandro Soliman!</i>

9
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:20,767
<i>- When did he disappear?
- It's been five months.</i>

10
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,267
<i> Who is Sandro Soliman?</i>

11
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:25,200
<i>Don't you ever mention
that name in this house.</i>

12
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:26,567
<i> This conversation is over.</i>

13
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,600
<i> Get out!</i>

14
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,067
<i> Go away!</i>

15
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:40,133
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

16
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:45,267
[WATER SPLASHING]

17
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:47,467
[SARI SQUEALING] Ah!

18
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,167
Congratulations!
The curse is gone!

19
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:52,000
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:54,567
[SARI GIGGLING]

21
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,333
- Did your grandpa tell you?
- No, I just know it.

22
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:01,233
I believe the ritual my grandpa
talked about is effective.

23
00:01:01,367 --> 00:01:03,500
The ritual you performed?

24
00:01:03,633 --> 00:01:05,667
My neighbors did
the same thing before.

25
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,700
Were they two friends
who also tried to lift a curse?

26
00:01:08,867 --> 00:01:09,867
Yes.

27
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:11,933
What happened?

28
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:15,700
Well, they became a couple,
and eventually tied the knot.

29
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:17,500
And now,
they have five children!

30
00:01:17,633 --> 00:01:18,667
- Huh?!
- What?!

31
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,200
[BRIGHT MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:20,367 --> 00:01:21,367
[SARI CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

33
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:22,200
Yes!

34
00:01:22,367 --> 00:01:23,800
Not only did they
cast out bad luck,

35
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,433
but they also found
each other.

36
00:01:25,567 --> 00:01:30,433
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
BY ANGELA KEN PLAYING]

37
00:01:30,567 --> 00:01:31,367
Wait.

38
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,100
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

39
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:35,500
Wait, what if?

40
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:36,800
[SARI SQUEALS]

41
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:39,533
What if you two end up
together, just like them?

42
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,167
Why? It's possible, right?

43
00:01:43,267 --> 00:01:45,900
You're friends.
Plus, you're both single.

44
00:01:46,067 --> 00:01:47,400
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

45
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:48,733
Universe!

46
00:01:48,867 --> 00:01:52,333
Did the ritual bring together
another pair?

47
00:01:52,867 --> 00:01:53,733
[SARI GIGGLES]

48
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:54,733
[JADE CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

49
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:55,633
Come on, Sari.

50
00:01:55,767 --> 00:01:59,233
It's probably a...
case-by-case basis.

51
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,567
I don't think Kiko and I
will share the same fate.

52
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,900
That's so silly, Sari.

53
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:04,033
Y-Yeah.

54
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:06,033
Not to mention,
removing the bad luck

55
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:07,667
is what really matters.

56
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:08,567
Shh!

57
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,067
["PAANO KUNG TAYO NA LANG"
CONTINUES]

58
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,367
Sir Kiko!

59
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,867
Sir Martin might be around
and hear you!

60
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:15,600
Okay, listen.

61
00:02:15,767 --> 00:02:19,167
Promise me, this conversation
never happened.

62
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:20,600
Okay, bye-bye!

63
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:33,333
- Ouch.
- Oh, sorry.

64
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:34,767
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Be careful.

65
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:42,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,233
[MONETTE] Hi, Gio.

67
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:39,800
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

68
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:49,400
[MONETTE] Now, let me see.

69
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:52,267
[KIKO] Let's eat?

70
00:03:53,367 --> 00:03:55,333
- Are you hungry?
- [JADE] A little.

71
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,200
- Where's the--
- Monette.

72
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,467
About the guest
who caused a ruckus...

73
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:01,267
About Chase.

74
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,433
[GIO]
His stuff is still with us.

75
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:09,867
Shouldn't we turn it over
to the local town hall?

76
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,033
Not now.

77
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:14,467
He's still our guest.

78
00:04:17,033 --> 00:04:19,467
Once he's sober, do you think
you can talk to him?

79
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:20,767
[MONETTE] Just use banana.

80
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:22,600
I don't think that's necessary.

81
00:04:23,533 --> 00:04:25,600
We have a bigger problem.

82
00:04:26,167 --> 00:04:27,100
[JUSTIN CLEARS THROAT]

83
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,167
The bank has
already sent a notice

84
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:30,667
about the hotel's debt.

85
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,033
Luna.

86
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,067
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

87
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,667
[JUSTIN]
Luna, we need to talk.

88
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,567
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

89
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:56,033
- Monette.
- [MONETTE] Oh?

90
00:04:56,867 --> 00:04:58,567
Are those two okay?

91
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:02,133
Sounds like they were talking
about the mess from last night.

92
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,100
They got into a fight?

93
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:05,600
No.

94
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:07,933
It's about Luna's friend who's
checking in with us right now.

95
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:10,067
He got drunk and became rowdy.

96
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:12,433
Friend?

97
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:16,167
Hang on, I don't think she's
mentioned a friend like that.

98
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:19,267
Well, I wouldn't be surprised
if you didn't know him.

99
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,267
The things he was saying
about Luna...

100
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,033
Even Justin got caught up
in the chaos.

101
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,400
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

102
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:27,933
A lot of things
have happened

103
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,533
when we were away.

104
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:32,867
Needless to say, they've
had a lot on their plate.

105
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:36,300
[JUSTIN]
Luna, we need to talk.

106
00:05:36,467 --> 00:05:37,933
What for?

107
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,300
So you can remind me
just how messy my life is?

108
00:05:40,467 --> 00:05:41,700
No, Luna.

109
00:05:41,833 --> 00:05:44,100
- I've learned about--
- No thanks, Justin.

110
00:05:44,233 --> 00:05:45,967
I'm fine with what I've heard.

111
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:48,367
Noted.

112
00:05:49,733 --> 00:05:51,467
By the way,
aren't you suspended?

113
00:05:51,633 --> 00:05:52,933
Why are you here?

114
00:05:53,967 --> 00:06:00,800
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,633
Tsk.

116
00:06:10,367 --> 00:06:12,133
We have a big problem.

117
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,833
We're behind
on the payment.

118
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:17,433
Two months late.

120
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:25,133
Is it possible to appeal
for an extension?

121
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:26,600
That's just
an extension, Martin.

122
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:29,000
We still need to find a way
to be able to pay them.

123
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:30,000
[LEON] At the moment,

124
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,733
money is only coming in
from hotel operations.

125
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:34,767
But the music festival brought
in a nice profit, right?

126
00:06:34,867 --> 00:06:37,433
Yes, but we had
to give discounts

127
00:06:37,533 --> 00:06:39,633
to everyone inconvenienced
by that dead rat.

128
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:42,000
And after the fiasco
involving Chase and Justin.

129
00:06:42,667 --> 00:06:44,800
We've already spoken
to Justin.

130
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:47,700
He's temporarily suspended
from hotel duties.

131
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:50,200
But that alone won't solve
our problem.

132
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:52,767
[LEON] So we need activities

133
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,300
- that are low-cost,
- [PHONE CHIMES]

134
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:55,700
but have a high return.

135
00:06:56,333 --> 00:06:58,467
Promos that will lead
to bookings.

136
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:03,167
Anyone got ideas to help
the hotel generate money?

137
00:07:03,733 --> 00:07:05,600
All suggestions are welcome.

138
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:07,667
[MARTIN]<i> Uncle, have you
</i> read the proposal?

139
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:08,867
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,200
<i> Do we have a deal?</i>

141
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:14,367
[LEON] However, we need to talk
before we pursue it.

142
00:07:15,100 --> 00:07:18,067
Yes. We'll decide
together as a team.

143
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,133
Martin?

144
00:07:23,267 --> 00:07:24,400
Huh? Yeah.

145
00:07:24,533 --> 00:07:26,333
Alright, I'll come up
with something.

146
00:07:26,433 --> 00:07:33,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:07:34,067 --> 00:07:34,900
[PHONE CHIMES]

148
00:07:35,067 --> 00:07:36,900
[RONALD]<i> Let's meet again.
</i> Bring Sari.

149
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:44,333
Sir, I'm really interested
in your bar.

150
00:07:44,333 --> 00:07:46,367
And from the moment I saw it,

151
00:07:46,367 --> 00:07:48,333
wow, I immediately saw
its potential.

152
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:49,767
[SCOFFS] It's true.

153
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:51,733
I just feel bad letting it go.

154
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:53,367
But family comes first.

155
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:55,933
I also need to move
to America.

156
00:07:55,933 --> 00:07:57,200
That's understandable.

157
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,767
So maybe we can talk
about the contract...

158
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:01,133
[JUSTIN]
Do they think I'd be sad

159
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:02,300
about being suspended?

160
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,267
I didn't even want
to be there anyway.

161
00:08:04,267 --> 00:08:06,267
Oh, wait a second, bro.
Yeah, yeah.

162
00:08:06,267 --> 00:08:07,400
[PHONE BEEPS]

163
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,200
- Bro, how are you?
- Bro.

164
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,267
- Where did you come from?
- From the hotel.

165
00:08:11,267 --> 00:08:13,767
- Anyway, this is Trixie.
- I know her.

166
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:14,900
Oh?

167
00:08:16,633 --> 00:08:18,267
Ah, she's the one
you were talking about...

168
00:08:18,267 --> 00:08:19,700
Mhm, that's her.

169
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:22,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:24,467
What did he say? What--

171
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:25,933
I'll go ahead, bro.

172
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:28,233
- Let's grab a drink later.
- Alright.

173
00:08:28,900 --> 00:08:29,933
Justin.

174
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:33,167
Justin, wait--

175
00:08:33,167 --> 00:08:36,767
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

176
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,367
What did he say about me?

177
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,767
[GASPS] Sir!

178
00:08:48,067 --> 00:08:50,033
This is more than my daily wage!

179
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,900
You don't want it?

180
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:53,867
Thank you, sir.

181
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,467
Thank you so much.

182
00:08:56,167 --> 00:08:57,467
Sir, do you want anything?

183
00:08:57,467 --> 00:08:58,800
I can get you coffee.

184
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,100
Or lunch? My treat.

185
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:04,033
My boss gave me an incentive.

186
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:05,300
You know what, just keep that.

187
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,300
Prepare for our next meeting
with Uncle Ronald.

188
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:10,133
We have another meeting?

189
00:09:10,133 --> 00:09:11,433
Shh! Oh--

190
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:13,433
Sari, what did I tell you?

191
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:17,000
[WHISPERS]
We have another meeting?

192
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,167
Yes.

193
00:09:18,167 --> 00:09:19,333
And you're coming.

194
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:22,800
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

195
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,333
What do you mean
you changed your mind?

196
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:27,433
We were this close to a sale.

197
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:28,767
- Sir?
- Sorry.

198
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:31,267
I think I'll just give it
to someone else.

199
00:09:32,067 --> 00:09:34,300
What exactly did Justin
tell you?

200
00:09:35,167 --> 00:09:36,867
Is that why you changed
your mind?

201
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:40,267
Actually, Justin is kind.

202
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:42,300
He's helped me a lot.

203
00:09:43,467 --> 00:09:45,100
That guy? Really?

204
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:47,700
It's not obvious, but yes.

205
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:50,967
It's actually the first time
he's asked me for a favor.

206
00:09:52,367 --> 00:09:55,167
A favor against me.
Am I right?

207
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:57,167
[SIGHS] Not really.

208
00:09:58,867 --> 00:10:00,833
I just trust Justin's judgment.

209
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:04,033
If he says it's okay
to sell it to you,

210
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:05,333
then I'll give it to you.

211
00:10:07,233 --> 00:10:09,867
So you mean I have
to convince him?

212
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:11,400
Yes.

213
00:10:12,067 --> 00:10:13,467
Justin is kind.

214
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:16,733
You won't have a hard time.

215
00:10:19,867 --> 00:10:22,067
Alright, kids,
just keep eating, okay?

216
00:10:22,067 --> 00:10:23,533
- [GIGGLES]
- Okay.

217
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:25,133
Thank you, Miss Jade.

218
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:28,033
Oh no, don't thank me.

219
00:10:28,033 --> 00:10:30,533
Thank Sir Edward.
He's the one who gave that.

220
00:10:30,533 --> 00:10:33,300
- Thank you, Sir Edward.
- Thank you, Sir Edward.

221
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,433
- Just eat, okay?
- Just keep eating.

222
00:10:36,433 --> 00:10:37,567
Thank you.

223
00:10:38,933 --> 00:10:40,100
Edward, pork buns?

224
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:42,833
Thank you.

225
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:45,533
Thanks for the lunch date.

226
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,900
Wow.

227
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:52,100
That's the first time
you thanked me.

228
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:55,400
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:59,867
You know, out of all
our lunch dates,

230
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:01,833
this one is my favorite.

231
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:06,433
I'm just not the one
you want to date.

232
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,200
What's that?

233
00:11:12,133 --> 00:11:13,967
Nothing. I said let's just
finish our lunch.

234
00:11:13,967 --> 00:11:17,300
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:19,433
Edward, are you okay?

236
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,233
Is there... something wrong?

237
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:27,367
I get it.

238
00:11:28,067 --> 00:11:30,067
So you're really not going
to share, huh?

239
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:34,433
Didn't you say...

240
00:11:35,967 --> 00:11:38,033
...we only share
what we want to share?

241
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,533
There's no forcing, right?

242
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:49,333
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,300
How are things at the hotel?

244
00:12:06,467 --> 00:12:07,567
Well...

245
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:09,900
...a lot of things
didn't go well.

246
00:12:12,967 --> 00:12:13,967
Like?

247
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:16,333
Well...

248
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,600
...a guest caused a scene.

249
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:21,400
But the bigger problem
is the bank notice.

250
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:24,267
But don't worry about that.

251
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:27,000
We'll handle it. It's okay.

252
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,367
How's your leave?

253
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:35,467
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

254
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:37,333
It's okay.

255
00:12:40,133 --> 00:12:42,167
I was able to do
what I needed to do.

256
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:48,133
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

257
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,567
Alright.

258
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:52,033
Let's finish this lunch date.

259
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:53,333
Someone might get upset.

260
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,367
Huh?

261
